Project 'Campain for Access to Information and Citizen Action' (Funded by the EUropean Commission within the EIDHR)

The project provides law and communications students with hands-on training and community outreach and education in freedom of information issues of public consern. The Campain provides citizens with knowledge, tools, free legal expertise and actual litigation in order to demonstrate citizens' rights in action.

> providing and management of overall Campaing' activities preparation and implementation, including the followings: 
- forming groups of law and PR students; 
- maintaing regular meetings (seminars, workshops) with them to develop a PR strategy and public outreach component; 
-maintaing  regular contacts with the Universities' Law Clinics and partner' NGOs (in fields as HIV/AIDS, advocacy for disabled, housing, labour and environmental rights;
> administrative and orzganizational assistance to the IIFD legal staff and law studentes on litigation support on behalf of the partners' NGOs;
>monitoring the progress of the project' activities and evaluation of the project' results;
>ensuring the project visibility (Social Media, informational leaflets, banners, articles);
>reporting;
